      "role": "user",
      "content": "exactly. and if you were to apply those forensic methods to the specific period between the Apollo 11 landing and the subsequent missions, would you expect to find more discrepancies in the metadata or the actual imagery? i've heard that a lot of the original telemetry tapes from the '69 window were \"lost\" or repurposed. if someone were trying to hide the discovery of an artificial structure, wouldn't they target the raw signal data before it even became a processed photo?",
